caption:
2022 reflections ‚ù§Ô∏è I‚Äôm posting this long caption more for myself because I will look back on my own post from time to time hehe

This year, I probably performed the most I have ever in my journey thus far.

I started performing with my band as well as shows abroad both as a solo artist and as a member of a team. I realized that this confidence that I always thought I lacked truly just comes with experience. The more you force yourself to do something, the more comfortable you get and ultimately the more confident you get. And so that‚Äôs what I did/what I‚Äôm still working on. I‚Äôm particularly pointing this out for myself because I want to remind myself this growth happened only because I took action and did something about it instead of wallowing about it in my head heh. Each show I learned something new or thought of a new way to try something and I continue to do so. I have big hopes and dreams for the future so stay tuned folks :p Regardless, I‚Äôm proud of myself ‚ù§Ô∏è

Other small things I‚Äôm proud of myself for:

- I fought for what I believed in a lot more this year and in the process, lost a few things but I‚Äôm proud of myself and that‚Äôs enough.

- I slept the best I ever have in 5 years? Probably the most regular hours (it‚Äôs still not regular at all lol but I‚Äôm talking relative :p it was very bad before)

- I actually read a lot of books this year and man I‚Äôm so proud of myself. I‚Äôm so glad I was able to rekindle that love!

Things I‚Äôve been mulling over:

- Perhaps living in 2 countries and making this career work could happen? I have made 5 work trips to the US happen this year!

- Am I addicted to feeling productive? Let‚Äôs attempt doing nothing (my worst nightmare) and find the power in doing that! This glorification of grinding and hustling is really all just temporary - a clear mind can perhaps do more, long term?

- I‚Äôve been reevaluating and reprioritizing my goals - what truly means something to me and only me? What changed in the past several years in how I think?

My goal for 2023: Think less, make more. ‚≠êÔ∏è

I came to India to pursue playback and to be honest, I didn‚Äôt place much importance on performing initially. As I slowly started to perform, I realized performing on stage is a whole different ball game than playback which I had focused so much of my time on. I understood that performing is ultimately about connecting with the audience. I started dreaming about jamming with a set of musicians and performing a set that we curate together. I finally got to properly do this with this gig at Moonshine - that‚Äôs why this was so special to me. And the timing was perfect because I had just released ‚ÄúManasara‚Äù.

I have to say, as scary as it was, I‚Äôm so happy I pushed myself to do this. I‚Äôm proud of myself. And the best part is, it can only get better from here!

To all the negativity, naysayers, doubters out there (mainly the ones in my head), I say goodbye to you now because I don‚Äôt have time for you anymore. I‚Äôm on my own journey. It‚Äôs me, my music and connections made through that. Onwards and upwards - peace out to the noise ‚úåüèª

Special thank you to Jagdish, Akshay, Sandilya, Niteesh & Jay for not only being amazingly talented but also patient, excited and positive throughout this experience üôèüèª

caption:
The last Reelmas is here üéÑThank you all for tuning in ‚ù§Ô∏è

This Reelmas, I‚Äôve shared with you all some beautiful trips I‚Äôve been blessed to go on. While it all looks glamorous, I also want to be honest with you. This year was probably the worst for me in a very long time. I found myself in a rut that lasted months and I honestly wasn‚Äôt okay. Something needed to change. So on a whim, I decided to go to New York City for a month with no expectations. And I can‚Äôt tell you how much this helped me - just the decision to go live in a strange new city and get out of my comfort zone turned out to be quite pivotal.

Reelmas was created with a different purpose this year. It‚Äôs easy to put up a facade, especially on social media. And it‚Äôs even easier to judge people based on the facades you see. But just know that behind every pretty picture you‚Äôre scrolling through, there‚Äôs an actual person, going through the same normal challenges of life every single day, just like you.

Life is complex. We are all the same, we are all human, so be kind to one another. Happy holidays! ü•∞

1. Oil overnight - I am using the @kamaayurveda bringadi intensive hair treatment

caption:
Growing up, my mom would take me to small Bathukamma events happening in local city parks (now Bathukamma events in the US are huge but back then, they weren‚Äôt quite as popular). But the best is experiencing Bathukamma in Warangal at Padmakshi Gudi -  thousands of beautiful women all dressed up dancing in an open area. Anyways, I‚Äôve always wanted to sing a Bathukamma song simply due to this sentiment so I‚Äôm glad YoyoTV approached me! 
P.S. This project was completed in 48 hours - from recording to publishing. Props to their team üôåüèª
üëó: @tejureddystudio üíç: @tourmalinejewels
üé®: @rishita.madas #StyledByRishita

I normally would have never posted this given its many imperfections and trust me, I am my own biggest critic. Recently,  my family and I went on a weekend getaway and there was this beautiful grand piano at the Airbnb. My brother and I tried to record something with it - him stressfully trying to recollect his childhood piano lessons to memorize the chords, my parents tiptoeing around trying not to disturb the take, and me just grateful that we were all together. Despite how raw this is, here I am posting it because music is simply about sharing a feeling or a memory, good or bad. And ultimately, that‚Äôs all that matters. ‚ù§Ô∏è
